{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MVeEWsupKB3yvhNxVrXqCV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need. The app:\n- Label: `app: demo-app`\n- Port: 5678\n- Serves at \"/\" with \"hello\"\n\nI need to create:\n1. A Service pointing to port 5678 with selector `app: demo-app`\n2. An Ingress with nginx class, host `app.example.com`, path `/svc`, rewriting to `/`\n\nThe key here is the path rewrite. The app only serves `/` but we need to expose it at `/svc`. So I need to use nginx's rewrite annotation to strip the `/svc` prefix.\nFor the nginx ingress, I'll use the rewrite-target annotation set to `/` with a path of `/svc`. This will handle requests to `/svc` by stripping that prefix and forwarding them to the app's root path.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":378,"cache_read_input_tokens":29922,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":378},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"711e221d-3d5e-4e12-9279-2d2ca4ecbd80","uuid":"338bcc45-bd70-4fef-ba2b-e6577f0f97a1","request_id":"req_011Cc59hYbZDvvEHiKFY9ZUC"}
